pageContext.claim: “Thanks to our pro-growth economic policies, our domestic unemployment rate reached its lowest level in over half a century.”
pageContext.analysis: The unemployment rate is low, but not quite that low. In May 2019, it dipped to 3.6 percent. That ticked up to 3.7 percent in August 2019. Still, the unemployment rate was 3.4 percent 50 years ago in 1969 and the all time low was 2.6 percent in 1953.
